{"questionId":"13108","questionHtml":"<p>Find the remainder when <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is divided by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {x - 3} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left(&nbsp;3 \\right) =&nbsp;27 -&nbsp;27 +&nbsp;24 - 24\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>27</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>27</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>24</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>24</mn>\n</math></span> = 0 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>remainder&nbsp;=&nbsp;0</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13108","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_10a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the remainder when p ( x ) is divided by ( x − 3 ) .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}